Thanks very much to those of you who responded saying that your domain
supports use of MX's.  Special thanks to Craig Everhart at CMU who supplied
a list of such hosts that he had compiled.

The current list contains 144 hosts or domains.  It's hard to say what
percentage of the namespace this represents.  The NIC table contains 435 lines
that correspond to this list and 5563 that do not (that's 7.8%).  However, much
of the namespace both IP and non-IP are not in the NIC table.

We have begun sending non-hidden domain names to these destinations as of today
(user@domain instead of user%domain@relay.cs.net).  I will continue to update
this list.  Please notify "can-do-mx@relay.cs.net" when your domain becomes
able to handle MX's (or when pieces of it can).

The current list is available from the CSNET Info Server.  Send a message to
"info-server@sh.cs.net" containing this text:
	Request: info
	Topic: mx-domains
	Request: end

or anonymous FTP to sh.cs.net and get info/mx-domains.

Thanks again,
Dan Long
CSNET Technical Liaison

